Delta Volume Analysis by Price Levels
Description

This project analyzes Binance AggTrades historical data to identify the most significant price level inside every one-minute interval.

For each minute, the algorithm calculates the cumulative Delta USD at every traded price level, identifies the strongest buying or selling pressure, and filters only high-volume market events.

The generated dataset can be used for market microstructure analysis, liquidity research, order flow analysis, and development of algorithmic trading strategies.

Features
Automatic processing of multiple AggTrades files.
USD value calculation for every trade.
Delta USD calculation based on trade direction.
Aggregation by minute and price level.
Detection of the strongest Delta USD level.
High-volume event filtering.
Automatic BUY / SELL pressure classification.
CSV export.
Processing Workflow

For every trade the application calculates:

Trade value in USD.
Trade direction.
Delta USD.

The algorithm then:

Groups trades by one-minute intervals.
Groups trades by price level inside each minute.
Calculates cumulative Delta USD for every price level.
Finds the price level with the largest absolute Delta USD.
Filters only high-volume trading activity.
Determines whether buyers or sellers dominated the market.
Output Data

Each detected event contains:

Timestamp
Price Level
Delta USD
Total USD Volume
Market Side (BUY / SELL)
